cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the impact of memory hierarchies on predictability for time-constrained embedded software. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.EM (Embedded Systems). The paper also discusses worst-case execution time (WCET) analysis, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of scratchpad memories and caches, which are both related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of memory hierarchies on safety-critical systems, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
